The paper proposes a new architecture for modeling distributed sensor networks using recurrent neural networks (RNN). This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.LG and cs.AI. The use of RNNs also suggests that the paper may fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of attention functions, which are commonly used in natural language processing and computer vision, suggesting that the paper may also fall under the categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and computer vision (cs.CV).
